About the job
Job Title : Assistant Manager SAP Environment Co-ordinator

Job Location : Bangalore

About Unilever

Be part of the world’s most successful, purpose-led business. Work with brands that are well-loved around the world, that improve the lives of our consumers and the communities around us. We promote innovation, big and small, to make our business win and grow; and we believe in business as a force for good. Unleash your curiosity, challenge ideas and disrupt processes; use your energy to make this happen. Our brilliant business leaders and colleagues provide mentorship and inspiration, so you can be at your best. Every day, nine out of ten Indian households use our products to feel good, look good and get more out of life – giving us a unique opportunity to build a brighter future.

Every individual here can bring their purpose to life through their work. Join us and you’ll be surrounded by inspiring leaders and supportive peers. Among them, you’ll channel your purpose, bring fresh ideas to the table, and simply be you. As you work to make a real impact on the business and the world, we’ll work to help you become a better you.

Unilever is the place where you can bring your purpose to life with the work that you do – creating a better business and a better world. We are looking for talents that would like to join this exciting journey with us.

Main Job Purpose
Technical Planning – Managing SAP environment across the templates;
Lead system upgrade, migration, improvement projects;
Keeping Environment Current (KEC) – Execution of KEC strategies;
Responsible for managing & planning the change technical demand for the environment;
Conducting the release gates & verifying the release deliverables;
Co-ordinate bug fixes, test executions (including regression testing);
Work with SMEs for coordination of cutover , go-live and PGLS periods.
Scope Of The Role

The role covers the following areas:-
Responsibility for System Performance KPIs
Ensure SAP environment performance KPIs and success criteria are established and followed for the SAP environment, relevant teams in innovation and services are coordinated accordingly;
Where necessary, initiate and manage projects to keep the KPI’s in agreed scale and even plan for further improvements in a proactive manner, engage necessary resources;
Gather detailed information on where KPI’s are not met & facilitate responsive actions which may then be transformed into improvement projects;
Work with all levels of contacts from cross functional teams for further enhancing the KPI’s and system performance;
Liaise with EC/Apps basis teams to ensure resilience of environments;
Work closely with other system architects, service delivery and security teams managers. Work with external/internal partners to learn about tools and trends. Use these learnings to influence senior stakeholders.

Housekeeping Activities
Periodically check, identify programs/transactions which are putting higher load on to the systems and execute projects to improve and optimize. Identify programs which are consuming higher computing resources and optimize them;
Coordinate Disaster Recovery tests for each SC1/DR1 services with Service Owner, lead technical readiness;
Plan and execute system refreshes, environment readiness for the projects;
Ensure housekeeping jobs are running as scheduled and new jobs are put into process as needed, ensure other housekeeping actions are also planned and taken as well, e.g. deletion of unused codes.Determine custom code programs which are not being used and retire them after consultations with stakeholders;
Manage Data Retention Policy. Ensure that archiving activities are executed based on the effective policy. Strengthen data retention policy by including additional archiving objects as necessary;
Ensure that improvement activities are carried out according to landscape methodology, agreed design, meeting Unilever global standards, security and performance criteria and General IT & SOX controls;
Interact with Enterprise computing and Application Services teams to support them in setting priorities and developing action plans for setting up housekeeping and monitoring jobs;
Support Penetration Testing across the templates.

Project Support and On boarding
Support innovation teams, in their project onboarding activities from environment readiness perspective;
Ensure necessary skills are established and training is provided to developers of the system so that any new program developed is fit for high performance standards;
Assist his peers & STS Director as required for landscape performance related topics.

Incident Management and Root cause analysis
Manage escalations regarding with environment management;
Work with other technical teams on issue resolution and RCA
Essential Skills
Complete higher education;
Advanced English;
Experience in managing and scaling large & complex transformation programs;
Experience in developing and scaling digital innovations;
Experience of project managing end to end multi-country, large scale and complex SAP data migration project experience;
Experience with AWS migration;
End to end knowledge of IT cost components;
E2E knowledge on SAP Basis, Application functionalities;
Agile & DevOps frameworks;
Experience of working with teams spread across multiple locations.

