About the job
You Lead the Way. We’ve Got Your Back.

With the right backing, people and businesses have the power to progress in incredible ways. When you join Team Amex, you become part of a global and diverse community of colleagues with an unwavering commitment to back our customers, communities and each other. Here, you’ll learn and grow as we help you create a career journey that’s unique and meaningful to you with benefits, programs, and flexibility that support you personally and professionally. At American Express, you’ll be recognized for your contributions, leadership, and impact—every colleague has the opportunity to share in the company’s success. Together, we’ll win as a team, striving to uphold our company values and powerful backing promise to provide the world’s best customer experience every day. And we’ll do it with the utmost integrity, and in an environment where everyone is seen, heard and feels like they belong. Join Team Amex and let’s lead the way together

Ignite your analytical skills to define the future of how we serve our customers. How we serve our customers is constantly evolving and is a challenge we gladly accept. Whether you’re finding new ways to prevent identity fraud or enabling customers to start a new business, you can work with one of the most valuable data sets in the world to identify insights and actions that can have a substantial impact on our customers and our business. And, with opportunities to learn from leaders who have defined the course of our industry, you can grow your career and define your own path. Find your place in risk and analytics on #TeamAmex.

Functional Description

The Enterprise Risk Management (“ERM”) & Strategic Initiatives team comes under the Global Risk and Compliance (GRC) organization and provides an independent view of risks faced by American Express. It focuses on core ERM activities (such as risk identification, emerging risks, enterprise risk policy, board reporting and others) and performing multiple critical initiatives pertaining to risk (including but not limited to: ESG and Climate risks). These responsibilities span the AXP Bank Holding Company as well as the subsidiary US Bank (American Express National Bank).

Environment, Social, and Governance and Climate Risk have recently emerged as a priority risk area for American Express. As a new risk focus, GRC has been charged with building out the Second Line ESG and Climate Risk management function. This new function aims to formalize ESG and climate work into the current ERM framework, as well as performing in depth risk identification and management processes. The new function will also be responsible in performing various climate-related physical and transition risks assessments and conducting climate change scenario analyses across different portfolios.

The Manager, ERM – ESG & Climate Risk Analytics shall report to the Director, ERM – ESG & Climate Risk Analytics to implement the following tasks and responsibilities:

Responsibilities
Leading a team of analysts to support analytical projects pertaining to ESG and climate risk.
Engaging in the development and/or improvement of ESG/climate specific risk methodologies to:
quantify climate-related physical and transition risk exposures in American Express businesses – using industry preferred methodology and ensuring alignment with regulatory expectations,
quantify ESG related metrics.
Performing activities pertaining to climate-related scenario analysis which include but not limited to reviewing approaches, scenario narratives, and results interpretation for climate risk manifestation across risk pillars and portfolios.
Ensuring the team members and leaders are advised and educated with the evolving climate risk management literature and analytical methodologies (e.g., approaches and tools delineated by TCFD, UNEP-FI, BIS, and other relevant literature).

ESG/Climate Risk Reporting:
Supporting the publication of the Organization-wide climate risk dashboard and report to the Risk Committees, Senior Management, and the Board, on a periodic basis.
Assisting in ESG/Climate disclosure related quantification processes (e.g., TCFD; CDP; other related ESG/Climate reports and disclosures).

Strategic Initiatives:
Provide subject matter expertise in climate risk identification, Quantification, assessment, and management in various critical initiatives or projects.
Working with Colleagues and Leaders across different BUs; as well as collaborating closely with members of the Climate Risk Working Group members to help implement American Express climate risk management roadmap and framework.

Minimum Qualifications:
Approx. 2+ years’ experience in Risk Management, Banking, Finance, or Management Consulting. Banking/Consulting experience pertaining to sustainability/climate change/climate risk is an advantage
Advanced degree preferred: Masters/PhD in business (e.g., MBA, Finance, Risk Management, Economics), atmospheric science, climate/earth systems science, hydrology, civil and/or environmental engineering, or other related fields;
Familiarity with climate risk analysis, including physical and transition risk assessments, industry standards in GHG emission reporting, TCFD framework, and other broader ESG topics;
Understanding of various general reference scenarios such as NGFS, IPCC, and IEA scenarios, and translation of climate risks into financial system impacts;
Strong organizational and process management skills, with proven ability to lead multiple priorities and complete deliverables under critical timelines;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, data mining and data processing experience;
Experience developing data visualization techniques and tools for communication to internal and external partners, (e.g., ArcGIS, Tableau, Alteryx, or similar);
Experience in SQL with operating in big data environments;
Experience with Python/SAS/R is a plus;
Sharp attention to detail and internal quality controls.

Leadership Skills:
Ability to lead and empower multi-disciplinary teams;
Self-motivated and team oriented;
Self-confident with a strong sense of integrity and the ability and eagerness to challenge and be challenged;
Unwavering sense of ownership over outcomes;

Communication:
Advanced communication skills and excellent PowerPoint skills;
Efficiently develops presentation materials with clear, concise, and compelling messaging for Senior Management, the Board, and external regulators;
Consistent track record to deliver high quality, error-free documents;
Excellent communication skills (both MS-PowerPoint and MS-Word).

Additional Details:
Base Location: Gurgaon, India
Workplace Flexibility: Potential

